6 AS INTRODUCED
6
7 An Act relating to schools; amending Section 2,
7 Chapter 281, O.S.L. 2023, as amended by Section 2,
8 Chapter 408, O.S.L. 2024 (70 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section
8 5-148.2), which relates to the School Security
9 Revolving Fund; expanding use of fund; removing
9 expenditure limitation; requiring certain amount of
10 funds to be allocated from the fund each fiscal year
10 for three fiscal years beginning on certain date,
11 subject to available funding; providing an effective
11 date; and declaring an emergency.
12
12
13
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14
15 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY Section 2, Chapter 281, O.S.L.
15
16 2023, as amended by Section 2, Chapter 408, O.S.L. 2024 (70 O.S.
16
17 Supp. 2025, Section 5-148.2), is amended to read as follows:
17
18 Section 5-148.2. A. There is hereby created in the State
18
19 Treasury a revolving fund for the State Department of Education to
19
20 be designated the “School Security Revolving Fund”. The fund shall
20
21 be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations, and
21
22 shall consist of all monies received by the State Department of
22
23 Education from:
23
24
24
Req. No. 2396 Page 1

1 1. Reimbursements, grants, or other monies received from other
1
2 state agencies and entities for school security;
2
3 2. Reimbursements, grants, or other monies received from the
3
4 United States government obligated to school security projects;
4
5 3. Gifts, donations, and bequests; and
5
6 4. Monies appropriated or apportioned by the Legislature.
6
7 B. All monies accruing to the credit of the School Security
7
8 Revolving Fund are hereby appropriated and may be budgeted and
8
9 expended by the State Department of Education for the purposes of:
9
10 1. Establishing and maintaining a School Resource Officer
10
11 Program; and
11
12 2. Providing physical security enhancements for schools
12
13 including, but not limited to, school resource officers, cameras,
13
14 gates, lighting, locks, doors, windows, security geofencing,
14
15 ballistic storm shelters, and mobile panic alert systems; and
15
16 3. Contracting with a licensed mental health professional to
16
17 provide counseling and social services to students.
17
18 Monies in the School Security Revolving Fund shall supplement
18
19 and not supplant existing school security funding.
19
20 C. Expenditures from the School Security Revolving Fund shall
20
21 be made upon warrants issued by the State Treasurer against claims
21
22 filed as prescribed by law with the Director of the Office of
22
23 Management and Enterprise Services for approval and payment.
23
24 Expenditures from the School Security Revolving Fund shall not
24
Req. No. 2396 Page 2

1 exce ed Subject to the availability of funding, Fifty Million Dollars
1
2 ($50,000,000.00) in any fiscal year and shall be allocated from the
2
3 School Security Revolving Fund and divided equally among every
3
4 public school district in the this state each fiscal year for three
4
5 (3) fiscal years beginning July 1, 2026.
5
6 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
6
7 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
7
8 of the public peace, health, or safety, an emergency is hereby
8
9 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
9
10 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
